  "prompt": "Which are the best UK universities for economics at undergraduate level?",
  "response": "The UK is home to some of the world's leading universities for studying economics at the undergraduate level. Here are some of the top institutions renowned for their economics programs:\n\n### 1. **University of Cambridge**\n   - **Program:** BA (Hons) in Economics\n   - Known for its rigorous academic standards and strong focus on theoretical and applied economics.\n   - Part of the prestigious Cambridge Tripos system.\n\n### 2. **University of Oxford**\n   - **Program:** BA (Hons) in Philosophy, Politics, and Economics (PPE)\n   - One of the most famous and competitive programs globally, offering a broad interdisciplinary approach to economics.\n\n### 3. **London School of Economics and Political Science (LSE)**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - LSE is world-renowned for its economics program, with a strong focus on research and practical applications.\n   - Consistently ranked among the top economics departments globally.\n\n### 4. **University College London (UCL)**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a strong program with a focus on both theoretical and applied economics.\n   - Located in the heart of London, providing access to numerous networking opportunities.\n\n### 5. **University of Warwick**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Known for its strong emphasis on mathematical and quantitative methods in economics.\n   - Consistently ranked highly in both national and international league tables.\n\n### 6. **University of Edinburgh**\n   - **Program:** MA (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a flexible program that allows students to combine economics with other disciplines.\n   - Known for its strong research output and international reputation.\n\n### 7. **University of Manchester**\n   - **Program:** BA (Hons) / BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a range of economics programs with options to specialize in various fields.\n   - Known for its strong faculty and research contributions to economics.\n\n### 8. **University of Bristol**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a comprehensive program with a focus on developing analytical and quantitative skills.\n   - Known for its supportive academic environment and strong graduate prospects.\n\n### 9. **University of Nottingham**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Known for its strong emphasis on applied economics and real-world problem-solving.\n   - Offers opportunities for study abroad and industry placements.\n\n### 10. **University of Bath**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Known for its strong focus on employability and practical applications of economics.\n   - Offers a range of optional modules and placements in industry.\n\n### 11. **Durham University**\n   - **Program:** BA (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a flexible program with a strong emphasis on analytical and quantitative skills.\n   - Known for its collegiate system and supportive academic environment.\n\n### 12. **King's College London (KCL)**\n   - **Program:** BSc (Hons) in Economics\n   - Offers a strong program with a focus on economic theory and its applications.\n   - Located in central London, providing access to numerous professional opportunities.\n\nThese universities are highly regarded for their economics programs, offering a combination of strong academic teaching, research opportunities, and excellent graduate prospects. When choosing a university, consider factors such as course content, teaching quality, location, and career support services.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
